{"id":15324,"date":"2024-04-25T03:24:03","date_gmt":"2024-04-25T03:24:03","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/sultan@brandsolutions.icu"},"modified":"2025-08-20T07:02:55","modified_gmt":"2025-08-20T07:02:55","password":"","slug":"mandatory-setups","status":"publish","type":"docs","link":"https:\/\/6valley.app\/documentation\/admin-and-web-application-configuration\/mandatory-setups\/","title":{"rendered":"Mandatory Setup"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"Map-Configuration\"><strong>Map Configuration<\/strong><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Client should buy Map API from Google for enabling the maps into the panels. Without buying those API\u2019s client cannot load Google map into the panels for selecting address. For generating map api key you can watch this video. Now go to your admin panel then 3rd Party Setup &gt; Other Configuration menu, here you will find two inputs for map api key client and map api key server. You can restrict the client with admin panel domain and the server key with your server ip address. If you don\u2019t want any restriction then you can use single api key for both field.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group doc-tip\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained\">\n<p><strong>TIP<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Recommended tutorial is below \ud83d\udc47<\/p>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-4-3 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<iframe title=\"How to Generate Google Map API Key and Setup in Flutter Project\" width=\"1200\" height=\"900\" src=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/kfHNfPEzSLs?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen><\/iframe>\n<\/div><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"Business-Setup\"><strong>Business Setup<\/strong><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Here&#8217;s where you can set up your general business and company details, including app download information, website colors, and logos. Additionally, you can manage payment, product, order, vendor, customer and delivery men settings, as well as shipping methods and invoice preferences, all in one place. For further details, explore the options available here &#8211; <a href=\"https:\/\/6valley.app\/solution\/#admin_panel\">https:\/\/6valley.app\/solution\/#admin_panel<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"Mail-Configuration\"><strong>Mail Configuration&nbsp;<\/strong><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Email create in cpanel &#8211;<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<iframe title=\"How to Create Email in Cpanel for 6Valley?\" width=\"1200\" height=\"675\" src=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/nG4cQlJrUiU?list=PLLFMbDpKMZBx3i9ukTW53Sx95poO-qPL4\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen><\/iframe>\n<\/div><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Email configuration &#8211;<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<iframe title=\"How to Configure Email in 6Valley?\" width=\"1200\" height=\"675\" src=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/DiSXEmOAvgE?list=PLLFMbDpKMZBx3i9ukTW53Sx95poO-qPL4\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen><\/iframe>\n<\/div><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"Firebase-Configuration\"><strong>Firebase Configuration (for notification)&nbsp;<\/strong><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>To configure push notifications, watch the setup video and go to Firebase Console:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Make sure you carefully follow all the steps shown in the video to avoid any issues during the setup.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Once configured properly, your system will be ready to receive push notifications through Firebase Cloud Messaging (FCM).<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<iframe title=\"How to Genarate FCM Service Token in 6valley\" width=\"1200\" height=\"675\" src=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/1FDtvgcZfI0?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen><\/iframe> \n<\/div><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Firebase Auth Configuration&nbsp;<\/strong><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>To enable OTP-based login, watch the setup video and go to Firebase Console, open your project, and enable the Phone provider from the Authentication \u2192 Sign-in method tab.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Firebase requires an active billing account to use Phone Authentication, so make sure billing is enabled in your Firebase project.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>In Firebase Console, you can also configure test phone numbers with fixed OTP codes. These allow you to test OTP login flows without sending real SMS messages or incurring charges.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Once configured, users can log in using their phone number and a one-time password sent via SMS, with Firebase managing the verification process on your behalf.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<iframe title=\"How To Setup Firebase Authentication In 6Valley\" width=\"1200\" height=\"675\" src=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/fho206IH8OE?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen><\/iframe>\n<\/div><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Addon Activation Process<\/strong><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>To activate addons, go to the Admin Panel \u2192 Addon Activation. Enter your CodeCanyon username and the purchase code of the addon you want to activate.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Once activated, the system will connect to the addons API, and all features for that addon will be available in your project.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<iframe title=\"How to Active Addons in 6valley\" width=\"1200\" height=\"675\" src=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/uBlazaL3wHI?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen><\/iframe>\n<\/div><\/figure>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Map Configuration Client should buy Map API from Google for enabling the maps into the panels. Without buying those API\u2019s client cannot load Google map into the panels for selecting address. For generating map api key you can watch this video. Now go to your admin panel then 3rd Party Setup &gt; Other Configuration menu, &#8230; <a title=\"Mandatory Setup\" class=\"read-more\" href=\"https:\/\/6valley.app\/documentation\/admin-and-web-application-configuration\/mandatory-setups\/\" aria-label=\"Read more about Mandatory Setup\">Read more<\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":3,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"","meta":{"footnotes":""},"doc_category":[187],"doc_tag":[199],"class_list":["post-15324","docs","type-docs","status-publish","hentry","doc_category-admin-and-web-application-configuration","doc_tag-mobile-application-mandatory-setup"],"year_month":"2025-11","word_count":458,"total_views":0,"reactions":{"happy":0,"normal":0,"sad":0},"author_info":{"name":"Sunny Sultan","author_nicename":"sultan6amtech-com","author_url":"https:\/\/6valley.app\/author\/sultan6amtech-com\/"},"doc_category_info":[{"term_name":"Admin and Web Application Configuration","term_url":"https:\/\/6valley.app\/docs-category\/admin-and-web-application-configuration\/"}],"doc_tag_info":[{"term_name":"Mandatory Setup","term_url":"https:\/\/6valley.app\/docs-tag\/mobile-application-mandatory-setup\/"}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/6valley.app\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/docs\/15324","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/6valley.app\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/docs"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/6valley.app\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/docs"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/6valley.app\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/3"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/6valley.app\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=15324"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/6valley.app\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/docs\/15324\/revisions"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/6valley.app\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=15324"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"doc_category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/6valley.app\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/doc_category?post=15324"},{"taxonomy":"doc_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/6valley.app\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/doc_tag?post=15324"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}